Life is made easier as I have my desk in the kitchen. Aided by an espresso martini today I have spent most of the day  planning menus, designing recipes and doing prep for my next few dinners. I‚Äôve churned sorbet, baked crackers for the cheese course and made stock. If anyone thinks that running a supper club is just something that is thrown together on the day, think again. When I started this wonderful journey 11 years ago there were 2 supper clubs in London, one in Wales and me. The lovely guests who have visited over the last few weeks have reminded us why we love what we do. 
I have tagged (tap the first photo for tags) all the amazing hosts I follow and admire in the UK and Ireland in this post and I urge you to seek them out and enjoy their offerings. Everyone is unique and cooks from the heart. I have decided that this year I need to reduce the number of dinners we host. It‚Äôs vital to me to love what I do and I am painfully aware that at the young age of 57 I need to be kinder to myself üòÇ . I have therefore posted all my dates to the end of June on my website. As well as the usual restaurant nights we are hosting the following special events;

7 March & 11 April, Steak Night
11 & 25 March, Curry

I‚Äôve had my teeth cleaned! I HATE going to the dentist. This isn‚Äôt unusual. As a child I had over crowding so every time I went to the dentist he  pulled a tooth out. It put me off. As I got older and tried to stay on top of tooth cleaning I started to resent the lecture I would get from the dentist. My teeth aren‚Äôt bad. I don‚Äôt have a single filling. It got to the stage where I couldn‚Äôt get a hygienist appointment without having to see the dentist first (¬£60). Then the hygienist started charging ¬£40 for 15 mins with accompany shaming session. All of which I resented. Whilst away earlier this year I took the plunge and visited the dentist in India. No lecture (just a reminder to use interdens) and an half hour cleaning session for ¬£12. I am now officially a tooth tourist ü¶∑ üòÇ #smile #dentist #confident #stoplecturingme
